20/02/2008
WASHINGTON, United States -- Defence ministers from Adriatic Charter Group members and NATO aspirants Croatia, Macedonia and Albania met in Washington on Tuesday (February 19th) with Deputy Secretary of State John Negroponte.
Albanian Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu and his Croatian and Macedonian counterparts, BrankoVukelic and Lazar Elenovski, briefed him on developments, five weeks before the NATO summit in early April.
Separately Tuesday, Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader said his country's accession negotiations with the EU may be completed in the first half of 2009.
He said this year the government is going to send 121 EU-integration-related bills to parliament in a major step towards membership.
(Javno.com, HINA, AFP - 19/02/08)
